The paper discusses the implementation of Binary Neural Networks (BNNs) which are commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV). The focus of the paper is on the efficiency and effectiveness of the BNN implementation, which falls under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), neural networks (cs.NE), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of low power devices, which could also fall under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC).
